com.mcc.ul
Class DioDevice

java.lang.Object
  com.mcc.ul.DioDevice

public class DioDevice
extends java.lang.Object

This class represents a digital I/O subsystem on a DAQ device. In addition to digital I/O methods, this class contains methods to access information and the configuration of the digital I/O subsystem.

To create an instance of this class, call the getDioDev() method of the DaqDevice class.

setTrigger

public void setTrigger(TriggerType triggerType,
                       DigitalPortType triggerPortType,
                       java.util.BitSet pattern,
                       java.util.BitSet mask,
                       long retriggerCount)
                throws ULException
Selects the trigger source and configures its parameters.

Parameters:
triggerType - Returns the TriggerType enumeration indicating the trigger type.
triggerPortType - Returns the DigitalPortType enumeration indicating the digital port type.
pattern - Bitset containing the digital pattern value. This value is ignored when triggerType is not a pattern trigger type.
mask - Bitset containing the digital mask value. This value is ignored when triggerType is not a pattern trigger type.
retriggerCount - Number of samples to acquire during each trigger event when retrigger mode is enabled. This value is ignored when Retrigger is not specified when dInScan() or dOutScan() is called.
Throws:
ULException
